================================================================================
DATA DESCRIPTION
================================================================================
Dataset: Deidentified_Dataset_N303.csv
N = 303 pharmaceutical professionals
Data collection period: 10 March – 15 April 2026
Format: CSV (40 variables)
Fully de-identified prior to analysis
Missing Data Handling Rule (IMPORTANT)
Missing values encoded as “2” (Gender) were treated as NA
No imputation was performed
Complete-case analysis was used for regression models only
All exclusions are explicitly documented in Supplementary Table S1
Variable Dictionary (Core Constructs)
Variable	Description	Type	Range
PILS	IP literacy composite	Continuous	0–100
IAI	IP attitude index	Continuous	0–100
IRS	Innovation readiness score	Continuous	0–100
IPI	Innovation practice index	Continuous	0–100
Diagnostic_Gap	IAI − IPI	Continuous	-40 to 94

All indices are formative composite indicators, not reflective latent constructs.

================================================================================
MEASUREMENT MODEL STATEMENT (CRITICAL)
================================================================================

All constructs are operationalized as formative composites:

Inter-item homogeneity is NOT assumed
Internal consistency metrics (KR-20, Cronbach’s α) are reported for transparency only
These metrics are NOT used as validity criteria
Construct validity is evaluated via theoretical specification and empirical pattern coherence

(Coltman et al., 2008; Hanafiah, 2020)

================================================================================
STATISTICAL ANALYSIS IMPLEMENTATION
================================================================================

All analyses implemented in:

code/Innovation_Capability_Analysis.py
Methods include:
Descriptive statistics (mean, SD, skewness, kurtosis)
Pearson correlations with Fisher z-based 95% CIs
One-way ANOVA + Tukey HSD
OLS regression with HC3 robust standard errors
Standardized coefficients (β*)
Partial R² estimation
Multicollinearity diagnostics (VIF)
Residual diagnostics:
Shapiro-Wilk
Breusch-Pagan
Durbin-Watson
Sensitivity analyses (5 alternative specifications)
================================================================================
NESTED MODEL COMPARISON (IMPORTANT CLARIFICATION)
================================================================================
ΔR², ΔAIC, and ΔBIC are used as descriptive model comparison metrics
F-change test is reported as a supporting diagnostic, not a causal inference tool
No structural or causal interpretation is permitted from these comparisons
================================================================================
OUTPUTS GENERATED AUTOMATICALLY
================================================================================

Running the script produces:

Table S2: Descriptive statistics
Table S4: Correlation matrix (Fisher z CI)
Table S5: Regression + ANOVA results
Table S6: Diagnostics
Table S7: Sensitivity analyses
Table S8: Convergent validity
Table S9: Distributional properties
